20:53.935 --> 20:56.478
Look at chapter six, verses nine and 10.

20:56.498 --> 21:00.863
It says, these are the generations of Noah.

21:02.024 --> 21:04.828
Noah was a righteous man, blameless in his generation.

21:04.888 --> 21:06.670
Noah walked with God.

21:07.311 --> 21:10.034
And Noah had three sons, Shim Ham,

21:10.242 --> 21:15.332
And as you keep reading through that chapter, it gives you all the details on the arch's construction.

21:16.034 --> 21:18.438
Verse 22 tells us this, Noah did this.

21:18.519 --> 21:20.242
He did everything that God commanded him.

21:21.144 --> 21:24.210
And then you go to chapter seven, and it says this, or can you verse one,

21:24.482 --> 21:27.426
Then the Lord said to Noah, go into the ark, you and all your household.

21:27.606 --> 21:30.430
I have seen that you are righteous before me in this generation.

21:30.751 --> 21:33.575
Take with you seven pairs of all clean animals.

21:33.635 --> 21:36.018
The male and his mate and the pair of the animals that are not clean.

21:36.258 --> 21:39.283
The male and his mate and seven pairs of the birds of the heaven also.

21:39.343 --> 21:42.307
Male and female to keep their offspring alive on the face of all the earth.

21:42.587 --> 21:47.234
For in seven days, I will send rain on the earth 40 days and 40 nights.

21:47.614 --> 21:50.759
And every living thing that I've made, I will blot out from the face of the ground.

21:51.259 --> 21:53.202
And Noah did all that the Lord had commanded him.

21:55.202 --> 22:03.756
I can't help but read this and put myself in Noah's shoes, which is worth doing whenever you find yourself kind of reading and working your way through a narrative portion of scripture.

22:04.256 --> 22:05.478
You see, it's crazy.

22:05.719 --> 22:09.965
When you consider what God has actually asked Noah to do, it's unfathomable.

22:10.286 --> 22:15.755
Like God has looked at Noah and he has told him to build an ark on dry land.

22:16.796 --> 22:18.038
Nowhere remotely close to water.

22:18.880 --> 22:22.866
And yet, Moses, Noah chooses to go for it.

22:23.298 --> 22:26.122
And it's not just that he chooses to build this arc.

22:26.142 --> 22:39.901
It's also a Herculean effort that is of epic proportion, like this arc, if we were to bring it into our modern measurement would be 450 feet long, 75 feet wide, 45 feet tall.

22:40.341 --> 22:46.410
And because it's a triple decker, it's got somewhere close to 95,000 square feet of total space to stand on.

22:47.151 --> 22:48.473
It's a big sundeck, you know?

22:48.513 --> 22:52.498
And yet what you know is that Noah chooses to go for it.

22:53.026 --> 23:01.800
even though it takes him at the very least 50, but more than likely anywhere from 100 to 120 years total to complete the total project.

23:01.820 --> 23:10.193
And so if you're in Noah's shoes, if you're considering his way in the world, how do you think people are engaging with this guy?

23:11.495 --> 23:13.197
It's never even rained on the earth.

23:14.018 --> 23:14.980
And he's building a boat.

23:16.462 --> 23:17.644
There's not a ramp around.

23:17.684 --> 23:19.727
I don't see a trailer for it.

23:19.767 --> 23:21.490
That was smart.

23:21.922 --> 23:24.426
Noah is not just controversial to the people around him.

23:24.446 --> 23:27.591
He's crazy to the people around him.

23:28.833 --> 23:33.300
And the craziest part of it all is it's all God's fault.

23:35.123 --> 23:37.967
God is the one that asks Noah to do this.

23:38.909 --> 23:42.234
He's the one to ask Noah to commit social suicide.

23:42.314 --> 23:45.259
He's the one that told him to risk his reputation.

23:45.339 --> 23:50.066
He's the one that has made him a local laughingstock to everybody in his hometown.

23:52.354 --> 23:53.655
How could God do that?

23:54.736 --> 23:56.738
That feels so unkind.

23:59.141 --> 24:02.183
Here's how, because walking with God can be costly at times.

24:03.985 --> 24:06.768
Walking with God can be costly at times.

24:07.749 --> 24:14.055
Like Noah, he lost every Instagram follower he ever had, because he would not stop posting about that arc.

24:14.075 --> 24:15.236
And yet he never wavered.

24:17.198 --> 24:21.522
He never questioned if he was supposed to do it.

24:22.210 --> 24:22.631
Why?

24:22.791 --> 24:25.376
Like what would grip someone like this to do that?

24:29.063 --> 24:31.308
It sounds so simple and yet it is still so true.

24:31.408 --> 24:32.410
He loved God.

24:34.273 --> 24:36.337
He loved God.

24:36.357 --> 24:42.850
I remember when Brooke and I started dating, it made absolutely no sense.

24:42.870 --> 24:44.914
Not because she is an amazing, she is

24:45.474 --> 24:46.375
All out amazing.

24:46.455 --> 24:48.198
It made no sense because I was a senior in college.

24:48.218 --> 24:51.803
She was a freshman in college and I had my whole life already mapped out ahead of me.

24:51.903 --> 24:55.228
I knew I was graduating and I was moving to take a new job into a new city.

24:55.569 --> 24:58.052
And it was everything the likes of which I wanted to do.

24:58.112 --> 25:01.638
And yet I couldn't get by the fact that I just had this loving feeling.

25:01.658 --> 25:03.861
You know, I needed to be near this girl.

25:03.921 --> 25:10.130
And so what I chose to do was incalculable to all of my peers.

25:10.498 --> 25:13.343
It felt crazy to the world around me.

25:13.403 --> 25:24.862
I chose to forgo a higher paying job in a better city fuller of opportunity so that way I could take a lesser paying job in a city that had virtually no opportunity because I wanted to be near to her.

25:25.643 --> 25:35.139
You see, I knew things could be better in my life, but she could not be any better.

25:35.159 --> 25:36.882
I wanted her.

25:37.122 --> 25:39.125
And Noah feels the same way about God.

25:39.165 --> 25:40.768
He's looking at his circumstances like, you know what?

25:40.788 --> 25:46.476
Yeah, like people could be nicer and life could be easier, but God, God can't be any better.

25:46.997 --> 25:48.139
He's everything that I want.

25:48.379 --> 25:49.521
He's as good as it gets.

25:49.801 --> 25:52.205
And I'm going with him no matter what the cost is.

25:52.505 --> 25:55.129
He knows walking with God can be costly.

25:55.790 --> 26:00.818
That's why it says of Noah, three specific things that he was righteous, blameless, and he walked with God.

26:00.838 --> 26:04.724
It says that he was righteous, meaning he knew how to relate rightly to God.

26:05.485 --> 26:06.066
In life,

26:06.178 --> 26:08.460
You relate differently to different types of people.

26:09.001 --> 26:16.669
The way you relate to your boss is different than the way you relate to your boyfriend, which is different than the way you relate to your parents, which is different than the way you relate to the male man, which is different than the way you relate to your neighbors.

26:18.071 --> 26:22.035
To be righteous is to relate rightly to God.

26:22.135 --> 26:23.737
No one knew how to do that.

26:24.998 --> 26:26.259
It says that he was blameless.

26:26.760 --> 26:32.466
That idea there is that his character was not flawed, like his inner man,

26:32.546 --> 26:33.968
had integrity.

26:34.088 --> 26:37.393
It's interesting, the Hebrew for that word blameless is the word tamim.

26:37.473 --> 26:45.105
And when you read Solomon's construction of the temple, he was to use tamim stones, stones that had no crack or blemish.

26:45.866 --> 26:46.968
They were to be blameless.

26:47.629 --> 26:50.233
Your life is meant to be a blameless life.

26:50.253 --> 26:52.195
And then it says that he walked with God.

26:52.216 --> 26:56.562
Like when everyone was walking away from God, no one chose to walk with God.

26:57.058 --> 26:58.620
He didn't pursue popularity.

26:58.640 --> 27:00.383
He didn't need the approval of man.

27:00.403 --> 27:01.445
He just wanted God.

27:01.465 --> 27:02.286
That's all he wanted.

27:02.386 --> 27:03.728
He wanted proximity.

27:06.172 --> 27:17.068
And because of it, what we know is that as the world grieved the heart of God, Noah pleased the heart of God, which raises a big question in my mind.

27:18.290 --> 27:19.251
How did he do it?

27:19.932 --> 27:22.616
Like, how did Noah do what no one else could?

27:24.018 --> 27:26.642
Well, it tells us, if you go to Hebrews 11,

27:27.010 --> 27:34.277
Verse seven recounts to us a couple of things about Noah, but very one thing very specifically that's important around how he was able to do this.

27:34.297 --> 27:45.368
It tells us by faith, Noah, being warned by God concerning events as yet unseen in reverent fear, constructed in art for the saving of his household.

27:46.329 --> 27:52.935
You see, Noah was able to do it because he had a reverent, a holy fear.

27:54.596 --> 27:56.178
He didn't act out of a fear of man.

27:56.802 --> 28:00.045
He didn't worry what everybody was going to say, or what everybody was going to think.

28:00.065 --> 28:04.030
He did not act out of a fear of the future, even though he had things he wanted to achieve.

28:04.050 --> 28:05.011
He was not concerned with those.

28:05.051 --> 28:06.212
He was concerned with God.

28:06.232 --> 28:08.374
He did not act out of a fear of failure.

28:08.394 --> 28:11.097
Well, what if I'm not able to achieve what God's asking me?

28:11.117 --> 28:11.437
You know what?

28:11.457 --> 28:14.461
Let me instead just try to preserve what I already have.

28:14.481 --> 28:16.563
And he did not act out of a fear of discomfort.

28:16.583 --> 28:23.410
Like he didn't just stay home, remain uncommitted, and binge watch the last three seasons of Survivor in prep for the 50th.

28:23.746 --> 28:24.727
That's not what Noah did.

28:24.767 --> 28:27.351
What Noah did is he feared God.

28:27.491 --> 28:29.354
That's where his fear was found.

28:29.454 --> 28:30.976
It was found in God.

28:30.996 --> 28:50.482
And the reason we know that is because twice in this story, twice, it tells us that he did all that God commanded him, which is impressive because God asks a lot and God expects a lot and yet Noah delivered on all of it.

28:50.978 --> 28:52.821
But that's not only why it's impressive.

28:52.841 --> 28:55.385
You want to know why it's also even more impressive?

28:56.467 --> 29:05.502
It is even more impressive because Noah did not know the specifics of how God intended to judge the world.

29:06.304 --> 29:10.431
He knew God was going to bring judgment, but he had no idea what it was going to look like.

29:10.751 --> 29:14.898
All he knew is God was asking him to build a big wooden boat.

29:17.666 --> 29:18.287
And that's it.

29:18.788 --> 29:22.154
He didn't have any clarity from God of what was to come.

29:22.394 --> 29:28.725
He just knew that God had asked, which is so important because Noah reveals to us that we don't need a great reason to go.

29:28.745 --> 29:31.730
We just need God's word.

29:32.511 --> 29:35.276
When God asks, we respond.

29:36.318 --> 29:39.063
Noah didn't need to be convinced that it was worth doing.

29:39.443 --> 29:43.410
He didn't need to be persuaded that it was going to

29:43.490 --> 29:51.364
Yield something, some kind of blessing in his life, and he did not need to worry about God, he did not need to worry about God preserving his reputation.

29:51.444 --> 29:53.568
Instead, he just needed God to ask him.

29:53.788 --> 29:54.750
That was reason enough.

29:55.651 --> 29:57.374
And so I need you to listen to me on this.

30:00.099 --> 30:08.754
I am so convinced for every single person in the room that God has asked us to do something.

30:09.634 --> 30:11.896
I don't know where you're at in relationship to him.

30:11.916 --> 30:13.738
I don't know if you've walked with him your whole life.

30:13.898 --> 30:16.000
I don't know if you don't care about him at all.

30:16.180 --> 30:24.308
But the truth of the matter is to every single person here, God has asked something of you.

30:24.328 --> 30:25.570
There are no exceptions.

30:26.531 --> 30:34.278
And yet some of you are waiting for God to give you all the details before you do anything about it.

30:36.240 --> 30:38.162
God has asked you to be honest.

30:40.258 --> 30:44.549
But you're waiting to see what's going to happen because your boss might actually fire you from your job if you come clean.

30:45.572 --> 30:53.874
You know God has asked you to go into ministry, but you're waiting for him to tell you how he's going to preserve your lifestyle because you don't want to give up the things that you've got.

30:54.082 --> 31:03.913
You know God has asked you to quit drinking, but you're worried about being quietly excluded from your friend group, and so you're hoping God will prove to you that you're not gonna have to give up what you have in order to be faithful instead.

31:04.233 --> 31:09.519
You know that God has asked you to pursue purity, but God, like, what's that gonna mean for my relationship?

31:09.580 --> 31:10.741
I really like him, I really like her.

31:10.961 --> 31:12.383
Are we going to be able to keep this thing together?

31:12.403 --> 31:18.610
Because we've bent some rules, we've compromised in the past, and I don't know if they're gonna like whatever parameters I have to offer.

31:19.491 --> 31:22.354
Some of you, you know God has asked you to come to region.

31:22.690 --> 31:30.680
And yet, you're not sure what it's gonna feel like to be 100% known and totally ousted in front of a group of strangers, and so you're waiting for him to reveal it.

31:31.040 --> 31:34.565
Others of you, you know that God has looked at you and he has told you to keep the baby.

31:34.605 --> 31:37.548
And yet, you don't know what that will mean for your future plans.

31:37.568 --> 31:43.676
Others of you, you know that God is asking you to admit where and when you lied to those people.

31:45.778 --> 31:51.986
But you're not sure what they're gonna think when you do, in fact, come clean, get honest, and tell the truth.

31:54.018 --> 31:59.105
You see, and this one's so important because I think it is so prevalent.

32:01.769 --> 32:16.448
We are often, instead of wanting for clarity of what God is going to give, we are wanting for certainty of what it's going to take.

32:18.972 --> 32:20.594
You don't want clarity of what he's asking.

32:21.922 --> 32:24.126
you want certainty of what that's going to require.

32:25.528 --> 32:28.954
And yet here's the thing that we learn from this story and you need to know for your life.

32:29.555 --> 32:32.440
God does not want you to move on facts.

32:32.460 --> 32:33.662
He wants you to move on faith.

32:34.784 --> 32:39.452
He does not want you to trust in your understanding of the circumstance.

32:39.472 --> 32:43.559
He wants you to trust in your understanding of Him and His character.

32:44.120 --> 32:45.202
He doesn't want you to

32:47.170 --> 32:59.584
to move forward without looking back and remembering what we've learned about his character that God is gracious and he's merciful and he's kind and he's just and he's compassionate to people.

32:59.604 --> 33:11.377
Because if you don't remember those things from the past what's gonna happen, you're gonna find yourself in a situation in the future where everything about your present circumstance is telling you God must not like you, God must have a grudge against you, God must in fact hate you.

33:11.417 --> 33:15.762
And none of that is true because everything he's done before would disprove that that is reality.

33:16.866 --> 33:32.327
And the reason we know it, for Noah and for ourselves is we can look to Jesus most of all and in Christ we can see someone who he walked with us at great cost to himself before we ever thought of walking with him at great cost of our own.

33:32.728 --> 33:35.071
You see Jesus, he moved into your neighborhood.

33:35.271 --> 33:42.661
He walked amongst you when you did not want him and he did so that way he might lay down his life and bring you into right relationship with himself and God forever.

33:43.562 --> 33:46.386
And if he's willing to do that to walk with you

33:46.594 --> 33:53.402
Even at great cost, we should equally be willing to walk with Him at great cost ourselves.

33:53.422 --> 33:56.525
Last point, look at chapter 7 verse 11.

33:59.789 --> 34:11.703
It says this, in the 600th year of Noah's life, in the second month, on the 17th day of the month, on that day, all the fountains of the great deep burst forth, and the windows of the heavens were opened, and rain fell upon the earth 40 days and 49s.

34:13.785 --> 34:14.706
Jump down to verse 17.

34:15.906 --> 34:18.508
The flood continued 40 days on the earth.

34:19.449 --> 34:23.073
The waters increased and bore up the ark, and it rose high above the earth.

34:23.113 --> 34:25.115
And the waters prevailed and increased greatly on the earth.

34:25.135 --> 34:27.077
And the ark floated on the face of the waters.

34:28.038 --> 34:33.202
And the waters prevailed so mildly on the earth that all the high mountains under the whole heaven were covered.

34:33.703 --> 34:37.286
The waters prevailed above the mountains, covering them 15 qubits deep.

34:37.707 --> 34:39.909
And all flesh died that moved on the earth.

34:40.569 --> 34:45.394
Birds, livestock, beasts, all-swarming creatures that swarm on the earth and all mankind.

34:45.474 --> 34:51.342
Everything on the dry land that whose nostrils was the breath of life died.

34:52.504 --> 34:57.470
He blotted out every living thing that was on the face of the ground, man and animals and creeping things in birds of the heavens.

34:57.791 --> 34:59.353
They were blotted out from the earth.

35:00.354 --> 35:08.786
Only Noah was left and those who were with him in the ark and the waters prevailed on the earth 150 days.

35:11.810 --> 35:15.115
Now when most people think of the flood narrative, this is the section that they think about.

35:15.155 --> 35:18.840
They think about waters rising high and mountains sinking low and creatures drowning in the deep.

35:19.140 --> 35:22.225
It's a really bleak image and it's really bad for God's PR.

35:22.405 --> 35:25.489
How can he be good and lose it like this?

35:26.210 --> 35:31.798
Is this a total overreaction in a necessary outrage, an irrational response to mankind's sin?

35:31.858 --> 35:32.359
No.

35:35.203 --> 35:37.466
God doesn't overreact to sin.

35:38.868 --> 35:40.210
We underreact to it.

35:41.794 --> 35:43.377
God does not overreact to sin.

35:43.497 --> 35:45.820
We underreact to this.

35:45.861 --> 35:50.809
You see, typically when we read this story, we question God's decision to flood the earth.

35:51.029 --> 35:57.820
And yet we do that without ever asking how God arrived at that decision himself, which is completely unfair.

35:58.461 --> 36:02.648
Like it's not right to take issue with God in the decision he's made.

36:02.688 --> 36:05.953
If you're not willing to really consider why he would have made that decision.

36:06.253 --> 36:09.138
And yet thankfully, this story tells us

36:09.474 --> 36:16.521
Like we can find ourselves just in verse 12 of chapter six, reading God's own explanation for why he chose to do what he did.

36:16.561 --> 36:27.571
You see, it says this, and I'm gonna read it to you from the NASB because I think that it helps us to understand much more clearly what's happening in the Hebrew.

36:28.932 --> 36:31.435
So check out the screen, unless you have that in your lab.

36:31.795 --> 36:39.122
It says this in verse 12, and God looked on the earth and behold, it was corrupt or ruined.

36:40.226 --> 36:44.512
For humanity had corrupted or ruined its way upon the earth.

36:45.553 --> 36:51.281
Then God said to Noah, the end of humanity has come before me, for the earth is filled with violence because of the people.

36:52.142 --> 36:56.067
And behold, I'm about to destroy or ruin them with the earth.

36:56.347 --> 36:57.349
Do you see what's happening here?

36:58.871 --> 37:07.442
It says that humans have ruined their way on the earth, and they have ruined the land of the earth alongside it.

37:08.770 --> 37:13.356
humanity's corruption is already leading to destruction.

37:14.378 --> 37:23.410
And so what God does, knowing how this is going to inevitably play out, he hands humans over to the very things that they've already begun.

37:28.176 --> 37:30.019
God is not the monster in the story.

37:31.801 --> 37:32.121
We are.

37:34.004 --> 37:37.428
I love the way Daniel Hawk commentator describes it.

37:37.468 --> 37:38.610
He says it like this.

37:39.938 --> 37:47.046
He says, the verse suggests that God has seen where the ruined nation of creation is headed.

37:48.107 --> 37:51.190
And he's decided to accelerate the process to completion.

37:52.572 --> 38:04.204
We're left with the sense that God is not so much sending the flood to punish the world as much as facilitating through the flood the inevitable descent into chaos caused by human destructiveness and violence.

38:05.406 --> 38:08.709
God ruins an already ruined creation.

38:08.749 --> 38:09.330
Do you see it?

38:10.402 --> 38:14.152
And in so doing, he creates conditions for a reordering and a renewal to take place.

38:17.601 --> 38:20.308
Which raises a really important question for us here at the end of our time.

38:20.348 --> 38:24.338
Where in your life are you rebelling from God?

38:25.922 --> 38:27.024
where you rebelling from him.

38:27.104 --> 38:36.717
I know it's easy to ask that from stage and to even receive that from the seat and just kind of think to yourself some of the things you know you should not be doing, get you find yourself doing.

38:37.098 --> 38:46.090
And yet here's the thing that I really want to lean into and I could give you a ton of mail as to what it looks like to rebel against God.

38:46.611 --> 38:48.594
Like for some of you it's your sexual ethic.

38:49.442 --> 38:52.586
You treat porn like it's some sort of normal self-expression.

38:52.706 --> 38:55.811
You're cohabiting with someone and you have no kind of commitment.

38:55.831 --> 39:00.798
You're redefining sex is purely recreational because your desire is to find what's right in your eyes.

39:02.240 --> 39:04.763
I could tell you that it's your radical individualism.

39:05.504 --> 39:15.378
No one gets to tell you who you are or what you do or how you get to be, which is a really dangerous place to live because it means that there is no authority in your life.

39:15.618 --> 39:17.360
And when there's no authority, there's no accountability.

39:17.801 --> 39:18.642
You are your own God.

39:19.042 --> 39:21.244
I could tell you it's your egotism and your pride.

39:22.505 --> 39:25.688
That you cut off people when they challenge you, you grow defensive.

39:26.069 --> 39:29.132
When someone tries to correct you, you think you know better than others.

39:29.772 --> 39:34.677
I could tell you that it's your goal-oriented idolatry because here's the thing, and this is particularly true for Christians.

39:34.737 --> 39:36.739
Rebellion sometimes looks impressive.

39:38.320 --> 39:48.370
And yet what you find is that your focus is on the money you make and the appearance you have and the influence you hold and it even bleeds into your religious reputation.

39:49.538 --> 39:51.560
I can tell you it's your personal passivity.

39:54.182 --> 39:55.604
This is such a prevalent issue in our day.

39:56.385 --> 40:05.513
It's such a prevalent issue in our generation that we will use our personality type as some sort of exemption from godliness and obedience.

40:08.076 --> 40:09.077
Let me just be real with you.

40:09.517 --> 40:11.319
Holiness is not a personality type.

40:12.640 --> 40:13.461
It's an expectation.

40:15.583 --> 40:18.866
Who God is is who you should be.

40:19.906 --> 40:21.147
You don't do that on your own power.

40:21.868 --> 40:27.234
You do that by way of yielding to his spirit, by submitting to his work.

40:28.956 --> 40:32.059
And often that begins by yielding to his work of conviction.

40:32.900 --> 40:35.363
You respond whenever he comes a calling.

40:38.526 --> 40:41.149
Here's why it matters that you identify where you're rebelling.

40:41.289 --> 40:44.413
Your rebellion will lead to ruin.

40:46.215 --> 40:47.316
Take a lesson from the dead.

40:48.177 --> 40:49.458
That's what happens to them.

40:50.114 --> 40:51.615
One man and his family make it out.

40:52.076 --> 40:56.100
Everyone else, because they rebelled when the days grew dark.

40:57.121 --> 41:09.092
They found themselves drowning in the deep, not of God's fury, but his passive wrath, giving them over to the very things that they wanted for themselves.

41:10.073 --> 41:19.282
You see, sometimes the very thing that you want for yourself is not the best thing for yourself, but everything God wants for you, it is in fact the best thing for you.

41:20.194 --> 41:24.359
you just need to receive it and respond.

41:26.401 --> 41:27.442
Here's the fear that I have.

41:31.987 --> 41:36.712
My greatest fear as I was prepping this is I could lay all this out to you.

41:39.175 --> 41:45.522
But some of you, you're going to wait until it starts raining to repent.

41:50.498 --> 41:52.020
You're going to hear the call of God in your life.

41:52.381 --> 41:54.164
You're going to feel the conviction of his spirit.

41:54.464 --> 42:00.193
And yet you're going to turn a deaf ear in a blind eye to what he's showing and speaking.

42:02.256 --> 42:08.025
And it's going to take those first drops for you to, to add last repent.

42:08.666 --> 42:10.709
And in that moment, it'll be too late.

42:11.851 --> 42:12.592
It will be too late.

42:14.054 --> 42:16.498
And yet what we know from this story,

42:18.562 --> 42:20.946
is it's not God's fury that brings the flood.

42:22.648 --> 42:23.529
It is his mercy.

42:25.092 --> 42:32.242
He takes an already ruined situation, and he redeems out of it a brighter future by finding Noah.

42:34.145 --> 42:35.587
And friend, he wants to do that with you.

42:36.889 --> 42:38.231
But here's the thing with that.

42:39.293 --> 42:45.162
Just as he was merciful then, he could be merciful today, but he will do for you what he did for them.

42:45.202 --> 42:47.986
He will bring you to your end.

42:49.250 --> 42:53.054
before he leads you to his beginning.

42:53.074 --> 42:59.440
In that end, it always looks like repentance.

42:59.460 --> 43:00.501
Last story and I'll get out.

43:01.542 --> 43:05.486
I was in college whenever I learned the story of Johnny Eric Zintada.

43:06.367 --> 43:12.814
If you're not familiar, Johnny was just 17 when she suffered a diving accident that left her paralyzed from the shoulders down.

43:14.195 --> 43:16.978
And yet in the almost 60 years since that accident,

43:17.730 --> 43:24.863
Johnny has used her story to teach not of God's fury against her, but his mercy towards her.

43:25.685 --> 43:28.830
Here's what she says in her booklet, Hope the Best of Things.

43:31.075 --> 43:35.222
I sure hope I can bring this will chair with me to heaven.

43:36.504 --> 43:41.714
Now I know that's not theologically correct, but I hope to bring it and put it in a little corner of heaven.

43:42.210 --> 43:50.219
And then in my new perfect glorified body, standing on grateful glorified legs, I'll stand next to my Savior holding his nail pierced hands.

43:51.620 --> 43:52.882
I'll say, thank you, Jesus.

43:53.663 --> 43:55.465
And he'll know what I mean because he knows me.

43:56.846 --> 44:00.350
He'll recognize me from the fellowship we're now sharing in his sufferings.

44:00.410 --> 44:04.234
And I'll say, Jesus, you see that will, Jer.

44:05.856 --> 44:11.282
You were right when you said that in this world we would have trouble because that thing was a lot of trouble.

44:12.610 --> 44:16.894
But the weaker I was in that thing, the harder I leaned on you.

44:17.815 --> 44:21.719
And the harder I leaned on you, the stronger I discovered you to be.

44:21.759 --> 44:31.227
It would never have happened had you not given me the bruising blessing of that wheelchair.

44:33.610 --> 44:34.230
Friends, listen.

44:36.813 --> 44:38.694
What may feel like punishment from God?

44:38.734 --> 44:42.578
Here tonight, it may actually be an invitation to you instead.

44:42.946 --> 44:49.780
because what we see from this story and what you need to know from your life is that God is not punitive in nature.

44:50.422 --> 44:52.666
He is redemptive in nature.

44:53.087 --> 45:00.323
And the reason we know that He is not wanting for your punishment is because He has laid that punishment on Himself.

45:00.383 --> 45:01.525
He has put it on His Son.

45:02.427 --> 45:03.890
You see, Jesus

45:04.066 --> 45:09.883
has done all that we could not from when we were quick to blame God for not caring Christ who was blameless.

45:10.365 --> 45:13.534
He proved how much he cared for us by pursuing us in life.

45:13.755 --> 45:17.426
For though walking with God is costly at times Christ walked

45:17.506 --> 45:21.451
with us at greatest cost to himself at even the cost of his own life.

45:21.692 --> 45:26.899
And though we may underreact to sin, Christ has reacted rightly in that he came to do what we could not do.

45:27.280 --> 45:29.443
He came to die where we deserve.

45:29.723 --> 45:31.706
And he rose forth in victory.

45:31.766 --> 45:37.734
So friend, if you feel like you're being punished by God, I would dare tell you you're being called by God.

45:41.019 --> 45:44.664
And the first step is a step of repentance.

45:44.704 --> 45:46.226
Let me pray that you would take that step tonight.

45:46.914 --> 45:58.490
God, I love you, and I'm thankful for these people and thankful God that God, though I, and though we can be better, you, God, cannot be.

45:58.550 --> 46:00.292
You are so good.

46:01.093 --> 46:02.014
You are so faithful.

46:02.535 --> 46:03.516
You are so kind.

46:04.077 --> 46:08.283
And God, you are so very slow to anger.

46:09.805 --> 46:13.270
You want all to come to the knowledge of your mercy.

46:13.370 --> 46:16.594
You want all God to bend the knee in repentance.

46:17.826 --> 46:19.729
So God, I'm asking that you would do that tonight.

46:21.732 --> 46:32.147
I'm praying, God, that here in this moment, as we turn back to worship, you'd save us from stealing out of the room and racing into our evening.

46:33.009 --> 46:41.842
You would save us from making excuses about why, God, we're not going to respond when we know it is you that is asking, that is calling, that is seeking.

46:43.063 --> 46:44.786
I pray, God, you'd save us from ourself.

46:45.314 --> 46:49.681
And for some of us God, that means tonight, we reach the end of ourselves that we find the beginning of you.

46:50.342 --> 46:53.266
God, meet with us now, move amongst us, please.

46:54.228 --> 47:00.117
And what we know, you are so very patient.

47:00.137 --> 47:02.000
And God, we're meant to be so very repentant.

47:02.881 --> 47:03.342
We love you.

47:03.723 --> 47:05.425
It's in Christ's name we pray.

47:05.445 --> 47:05.906
Amen.

